The paper deals with collision avoidance in collaborative robotics, which is a key topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The study also focuses on the interaction between humans and robots, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper proposes a methodology for achieving collision avoidance by using sensors and mathematical representations, which can be classified under systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of computer vision for obstacle detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV).
